
======================================================================
PERSIST-001 Systemd service creation in install [CRITICAL]
======================================================================

Category:
  Persistence  (detector: rules)

Description:
  Creating systemd services in install scripts enables persistence.
  Used in 2018 xeactor and 2025 CHAOS RAT attacks.

Recommendation:
  Services should be enabled by the user, not automatically

CWE: CWE-506

Real-World Context:
  Systemd persistence was used in both the 2018 xeactor attack
  (timers running every 360 seconds) and the July 2025 CHAOS RAT
  attack (services running at boot as default.target dependency).

Detection Patterns:
  - systemctl\s+(enable|start|daemon-reload)
  - /etc/systemd/system/
  - ~/.config/systemd/user/

Related Codes:
  PERSIST-002, PERSIST-003, PERSIST-004, PERSIST-006

======================================================================
